#!/usr/local/projects/routing/help/html_filter.pl
<h2 align=center>Help for the "Route" search menu</h2>
You can reach this menu by clicking on the 'Routes' button
at the footer of this application.
<p>The Route search menu allows you to search through all the
routes you have access to, and select which one to view.
<p>
The header for the search table shows the description of each of the columns.
If you click on the column header, you can enter a value and only show
routes with the specified value in that field.
<p>
Values in the search output are clickable:
<ul>
<li>Clicking on a <a href="record_Route.cgi">route</a>'s name will view information about
    that route.
<li>Clicking the <a href="record_Distributor.cgi">distributor</a> will show you information about that distributor.
<li>Clicking the <a href="record_Staff.cgi">driver</a> will show you information about the last driver of
    that route.
<li>Clicking the <a href="field_Route_Source.cgi">source</a> will show you information about the route by which
    food for this route got from upstream distributor to the current
    distributor.
</ul>

